1
00:01:44,416 --> 00:01:47,500
Igarashi, you're crazy.

2
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:49,500
You're really gonna
use that dorky keychain

3
00:01:49,583 --> 00:01:51,500
Serinuma gave us?

4
00:01:51,583 --> 00:01:52,916
Ah. Well, yeah.

5
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,458
It was a present.

6
00:01:54,541 --> 00:01:55,875
Why is that crazy?

7
00:01:55,958 --> 00:01:58,166
Dude, are you serious?

8
00:01:58,250 --> 00:02:00,541
[SERINUMA] These are the
new mini action figures!

9
00:02:00,625 --> 00:02:02,416
This is the
first one I've held!

10
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,750
Mini Shion is adorable!

11
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:07,291
As a thank you
for this evening,

12
00:02:07,375 --> 00:02:09,041
I'd like all of you to have one.

13
00:02:09,125 --> 00:02:11,041
Tonight was so special to me.

14
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:13,458
[laughs]

15
00:02:19,958 --> 00:02:22,000
She gave us matching
anime character keychains!

16
00:02:22,083 --> 00:02:23,666
I'm not gonna be
caught dead with that!

17
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:25,750
[laughs]

18
00:02:25,833 --> 00:02:27,625
[NANASHIMA] You don't see
me laughing about it.

19
00:02:27,708 --> 00:02:29,333
Guess she wants the four
of us walking around

20
00:02:29,416 --> 00:02:31,833
showcasing those things
like we're her little fanclub?

21
00:02:31,916 --> 00:02:32,958
What a turn-off.

22
00:02:33,041 --> 00:02:35,166
I dunno.
It's kinda interesting.

23
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:36,291
No, it's dumb.

24
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:38,083
Maybe you should
go ahead and give up.

25
00:02:38,166 --> 00:02:41,250
If you back out, that's one less
guy I have to compete with.

26
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:44,791
Yeah. You'd love for me
to do that, wouldn't ya?

27
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:45,791
[NAKANO]
Comin' in!

28
00:02:45,875 --> 00:02:47,833
Leave it to me!

29
00:02:47,916 --> 00:02:48,833
[grunts]

30
00:02:48,916 --> 00:02:51,625
[GIRLS cheering]

31
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:56,541
[GIRLS]
That was awesome!

32
00:02:56,625 --> 00:02:58,041
Go Serinuma!

33
00:02:58,125 --> 00:02:59,541
I always knew you
were pretty athletic,

34
00:02:59,625 --> 00:03:01,375
but I had no idea
you were this good!

35
00:03:01,458 --> 00:03:02,958
Those moves were impressive!

36
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:04,458
My body feels so light!

37
00:03:04,541 --> 00:03:06,791
I could play any sport I want!

38
00:03:06,875 --> 00:03:09,416
Wow... let's not
get ahead of ourselves.

39
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,708
[NANASHIMA]
Now that I think about it,

40
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:13,541
she was always good at
those jumping exercises.

41
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:16,833
They were intense.

42
00:03:17,583 --> 00:03:18,916
[clapping]

43
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,916
I've never seen anyone
pull off a receive like that!

44
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,041
I've never seen
anyone suck up so much.

45
00:03:25,208 --> 00:03:26,666
The soccer club needs help?

46
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:27,875
That's too bad!

47
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:29,000
What happened?

48
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:29,875
Well...

49
00:03:29,958 --> 00:03:31,250
Normally we have eleven members,

50
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:33,208
which is just enough
to play a game.

51
00:03:33,291 --> 00:03:34,583
We have a practice
match next weekend,

52
00:03:34,666 --> 00:03:36,208
but we're down one player.

53
00:03:36,291 --> 00:03:37,916
I got injured.

54
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,458
[GIRL STUDENT 02D] Since you
seem so good at sports,

55
00:03:39,541 --> 00:03:42,000
we were wondering if you could
take her spot for the game.

56
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:43,375
We'd be so grateful!

57
00:03:43,458 --> 00:03:44,708
[GIRL STUDENT 02E]
Please!

58
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:46,875
You assumed she
could play soccer?

59
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:49,625
I've never seen Serinuma
kick a ball in her life.

60
00:03:49,708 --> 00:03:51,083
Okay!

61
00:03:51,166 --> 00:03:51,791
Huh?!

62
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:52,833
You really will?

63
00:03:52,916 --> 00:03:54,666
Thanks a lot!
You're a lifesaver!

64
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:56,000
Uh, wait a second.

65
00:03:56,083 --> 00:03:58,000
Maybe think about it a
little before you say yes.

66
00:03:58,083 --> 00:03:59,458
It'll be fine!

67
00:03:59,541 --> 00:04:01,958
Believe it or not, I actually
know a lot about soccer!

68
00:04:02,041 --> 00:04:03,125
Huh?!

69
00:04:03,208 --> 00:04:04,916
I'm a fan of...
<i>Captain Tsubasa</i> ,

70
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,041
<i>Inazuma Eleven</i> ,
and <i>Giant Killing</i> !

71
00:04:07,125 --> 00:04:08,750
[NAKANO gasps]

72
00:04:12,041 --> 00:04:14,000
A soccer game!
Are you prepared to compete?

73
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:15,416
Sure am!

74
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,416
I've spent years studying
by watching sports anime!

75
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:18,625
[IGARASHI]
Wow.

76
00:04:18,708 --> 00:04:19,916
[SHINOMIYA]
Better than nothing.

77
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,666
[NANASHIMA]
Is this chick for real?

78
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:23,666
But still... It'll be
my first time playing,

79
00:04:23,750 --> 00:04:27,541
so I definitely want to
squeeze in a practice or two.

80
00:04:27,625 --> 00:04:29,375
Feel free to skip the
history club meetings

81
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:30,958
this week while you're training.

82
00:04:31,041 --> 00:04:32,708
I'll cheer you on.

83
00:04:32,791 --> 00:04:35,416
I'm supporting you too!
I'll even watch the game!

84
00:04:37,083 --> 00:04:38,666
Would you allow me to coach you?

85
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:40,291
We could run a few
drills after school

86
00:04:40,375 --> 00:04:41,750
and work on your technique.

87
00:04:41,833 --> 00:04:43,625
Yes! That's perfect!

88
00:04:43,708 --> 00:04:45,750
You guys are making me
so excited to do this!

89
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:47,333
I appreciate your support!

90
00:04:48,291 --> 00:04:49,666
[NANASHIMA]
This is just sad.

91
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:51,125
[IGARASHI]
Just one problem.

92
00:04:51,208 --> 00:04:53,583
I have my own practice so
I'll have to duck out early.

93
00:04:53,666 --> 00:04:55,916
But I bet Nanashima
could take it from there.

94
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,708
He used to play soccer way back.

95
00:04:57,791 --> 00:05:00,125
Yeah, there's no way
I'm doin' that.

96
00:05:00,208 --> 00:05:02,208
It takes years to
develop that kinda stuff.

97
00:05:02,291 --> 00:05:03,750
Doesn't happen overnight.

98
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:04,916
You let her on the field now,

99
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,833
and she's gonna slow
the whole team down.

100
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:08,291
Mark my words.

101
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:10,041
I'm gonna spend the
whole week practicing

102
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:11,958
so I'll be ready for anything.

103
00:05:12,041 --> 00:05:13,708
Just take it from Tsubasa!

104
00:05:13,791 --> 00:05:15,583
"The ball is my friend"... Yep!

105
00:05:17,291 --> 00:05:18,958
Fangirling over
an anime about soccer

106
00:05:19,041 --> 00:05:20,083
doesn't mean you
can play the game!

107
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:21,291
You'll look like an idiot!

108
00:05:21,375 --> 00:05:22,875
An underdog can rise
to the top if they put

109
00:05:22,958 --> 00:05:24,208
their heart into the work!

110
00:05:24,291 --> 00:05:25,916
You planning on having
a little training montage

111
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,375
or somethin'?

112
00:05:27,458 --> 00:05:29,250
You need to wake up and stop
living in a fantasy world!

113
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:31,250
Why are you being
so heartless, Nanashima?

114
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:33,000
Let's all calm down. It's okay.

115
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:34,333
Yeah, take it easy!

116
00:05:34,416 --> 00:05:35,958
No reason to get this upset.

117
00:05:36,041 --> 00:05:39,041
[NANASHIMA, SERINUMA growl]

118
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:42,875
I'm not gonna have any
part in this in this joke.

119
00:05:42,958 --> 00:05:44,333
Do what you want.

120
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:46,250
[SERINUMA]
What's his problem?

121
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:47,791
I don't care what he says!

122
00:05:47,875 --> 00:05:51,250
I'm going to put my all into
this and prove him wrong!

123
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:52,875
I can do it!

124
00:05:54,125 --> 00:05:55,083
[SERINUMA]
Nice to meet you!

125
00:05:55,166 --> 00:05:57,333
[SOCCER TEAM]
Thanks for coming!

126
00:05:57,416 --> 00:06:00,166
All right, let's kick things off
with some warm-ups! Cool?

127
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,166
[SERINUMA]
Okay!

128
00:06:01,250 --> 00:06:02,291
We'll start with some stretches,

129
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:04,041
then its twenty laps
around the school.

130
00:06:04,125 --> 00:06:05,250
I'm so dead.

131
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:08,333
[SOCCER TEAM]
Fight! On! Fight! On!

132
00:06:08,416 --> 00:06:10,541
Fight! On! Fight! On!

133
00:06:10,625 --> 00:06:11,375
[SOCCER PLAYER 02A]
Okay!

134
00:06:11,458 --> 00:06:12,916
Sit-ups and reserve sit-ups!

135
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,208
Five sets of twenty!

136
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:16,250
Put your hands
behind your head

137
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:17,833
and keep your legs together.

138
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:21,666
[SOCCER PLAYER 02A] Next is
two sets of 10 push-ups!

139
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:25,625
[SOCCER PLAYER 02A]
Deep stretches now!

140
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:27,541
I'm dying!

141
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:29,041
[SOCCER PLAYER 02A]
Time to start practice!

142
00:06:31,458 --> 00:06:32,958
[SOCCER PLAYER 02A]
That's all for today, ladies!

143
00:06:33,041 --> 00:06:35,791
[SOCCER TEAM cheering]

144
00:06:35,875 --> 00:06:36,958
Your first practice.

145
00:06:37,041 --> 00:06:38,291
Well, how are you feeling?

146
00:06:38,375 --> 00:06:40,416
I'm... great, why do you ask?

147
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,750
[IGARASHI] You
look like a newborn giraffe

148
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:43,125
learning how to walk.

149
00:06:44,541 --> 00:06:46,500
[SERINUMA]
I feel... fantastic!

150
00:06:46,583 --> 00:06:47,708
[SERINUMA]
I'm a filthy liar!

151
00:06:47,791 --> 00:06:48,750
This is ridiculous!

152
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,541
I've never been
an outdoor person!

153
00:06:50,625 --> 00:06:52,541
I don't do sports!
I don't do sweating!

154
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,291
I don't even think
I have muscles!

155
00:06:54,375 --> 00:06:57,541
My body will never
forgive me for this abuse!

156
00:06:57,625 --> 00:06:59,875
Maybe you should take it easy
for the rest of the night.

157
00:06:59,958 --> 00:07:01,750
I got this! Bring it on!

158
00:07:07,208 --> 00:07:08,583
That's not too tight, is it?

159
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:10,333
Wrapping your foot limits
the range of motion

160
00:07:10,416 --> 00:07:12,750
so you'll be less
likely to get a sprain.

161
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:14,833
Thanks! That's much better!

162
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:16,666
So glad we're on
the health committee!

163
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:18,750
You're the best, Shinomiya!

164
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,375
Well, um...
It's not a big deal.

165
00:07:22,458 --> 00:07:24,083
I brought refreshments.

166
00:07:24,166 --> 00:07:25,833
I never even thought of that!

167
00:07:35,541 --> 00:07:38,208
Hey, so... How do you
think she's doing?

168
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:39,875
Who? Serinuma?

169
00:07:39,958 --> 00:07:41,041
Yeah, her.

170
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:42,708
[GIRL STUDENT 02E]
Ugh. She's terrible.

171
00:07:42,791 --> 00:07:44,333
[GIRL STUDENT 02D] Maybe we
should look for someone else.

172
00:07:44,416 --> 00:07:45,791
She hasn't improved at all!

173
00:07:45,875 --> 00:07:47,375
Yeah.

174
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:48,875
Do you think we'll be able to
find someone last minute though?

175
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:51,291
I guess anyone would
be better than she is.

176
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:52,375
[BOTH gasp]

177
00:07:52,458 --> 00:07:53,625
You asked for her help.

178
00:07:53,708 --> 00:07:55,708
Drop the attitude
and be grateful.

179
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:07,208
[NANASHIMA] Crap.
Why did I take up for her?

180
00:08:07,291 --> 00:08:09,625
It doesn't have anything
to do with me.

181
00:08:18,708 --> 00:08:20,625
[SERINUMA grunts]

182
00:08:27,625 --> 00:08:28,583
[SERINUMA]
Gah!

183
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:31,583
My face!

184
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:33,333
[whining]

185
00:08:33,416 --> 00:08:34,708
What was that supposed to be?!

186
00:08:34,791 --> 00:08:36,208
Why are you out
here goofing around?

187
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:38,375
Why are you out
here watching me?!

188
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:39,916
I swear I'm trying my best.

189
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,083
Every time I kick the ball,

190
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:43,125
it flies back and
smacks me in the head!

191
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:47,041
Every time?
That's actually impressive.

192
00:08:47,125 --> 00:08:49,541
I guess the ball doesn't
want to be away from me.

193
00:08:49,625 --> 00:08:50,583
We're close.

194
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:51,875
[NANASHIMA]
No, you just suck.

195
00:08:51,958 --> 00:08:52,958
Yeah. I guess.

196
00:08:53,041 --> 00:08:54,333
I'll keep practicing.

197
00:08:56,125 --> 00:08:58,583
[NANASHIMA] Now I know
why they called her terrible.

198
00:08:58,666 --> 00:08:59,708
Listen.

199
00:08:59,791 --> 00:09:01,666
Maybe... You should just quit.

200
00:09:03,083 --> 00:09:04,916
You don't have to go
through with this thing.

201
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,708
Even if you spent all
your time practicing,

202
00:09:06,791 --> 00:09:09,750
you wouldn't be able to keep
up with the rest of them.

203
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:10,791
[SERINUMA]
No.

204
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:13,916
[SERINUMA] You were right
about everything.

205
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,500
I wasn't prepared
for this at all.

206
00:09:15,583 --> 00:09:17,083
It's a lot of work.

207
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:19,500
The other girls on the team have
been playing soccer for years.

208
00:09:19,583 --> 00:09:21,458
I can't catch up to them.

209
00:09:21,541 --> 00:09:23,708
It's my responsibility
to finish this.

210
00:09:23,791 --> 00:09:25,458
I can't let the team down!

211
00:09:27,791 --> 00:09:28,875
[NANASHIMA]
Look at her.

212
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:33,958
[NANASHIMA]
What choice do I have?

213
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:35,791
Give it another try.

214
00:09:35,875 --> 00:09:37,625
You're probably doing somethin'
weird with your foot

215
00:09:37,708 --> 00:09:39,125
when you go for the kick.

216
00:09:39,208 --> 00:09:41,333
I won't know for sure unless
I watch your follow-through.

217
00:09:42,708 --> 00:09:44,375
You said you don't
wanna quit, right?

218
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:46,125
Then I'll do what
I can to help you.

219
00:09:46,208 --> 00:09:47,500
Let's figure this out.

220
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:53,458
[IGARASHI]
What's Nana doing here?

221
00:09:53,541 --> 00:09:54,500
I wonder...

222
00:09:54,583 --> 00:09:56,000
They had that huge fight,

223
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:58,625
but it didn't take him long to
come crawling back to her.

224
00:09:58,708 --> 00:09:59,875
Let's be kind.

225
00:09:59,958 --> 00:10:02,416
It's a beautiful thing
when people reconnect.

226
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,916
Good for them.

227
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,291
[whistle blows]

228
00:10:06,375 --> 00:10:07,375
[FEMALE REF 02A]
Time out!

229
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:14,666
They're in stoppage time now,
and still down one point.

230
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:17,166
There's less than two
minutes left in the game.

231
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:20,250
What will they do?
This'll be hard to pull off.

232
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:22,125
I think I have an idea.

233
00:10:22,208 --> 00:10:24,958
When we get the chance... will
you pass it to me at throw-in?

234
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,166
What are you gonna do?

235
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:28,166
It's too late to save
the game, Serinuma!

236
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:29,666
[SERINUMA]
We can't slow down now!

237
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:33,250
Let's give them all we've got
until the inning is over!

238
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:34,916
[GIRL STUDENT 02D]
Soccer doesn't have innings.

239
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,000
[SOCCER PLAYER 02A] But she's
right about everything else!

240
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:42,458
I can't believe they're
this close to winning.

241
00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:44,708
If they can clear
the ball, it'll be over.

242
00:10:47,458 --> 00:10:48,833
[MUTSUMI]
Serinuma got it.

243
00:10:48,916 --> 00:10:50,666
This is her chance
to win it all.

244
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,541
All she needs is one good kick.

245
00:10:54,666 --> 00:10:56,458
[IGARASHI]
That's the wrong direction!

246
00:10:57,333 --> 00:10:58,333
[GROUP gasps]

247
00:10:58,416 --> 00:11:00,375
She wasn't aiming at all!

248
00:11:10,458 --> 00:11:11,916
[whistle blows]

249
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,166
[SOCCER TEAM cheers]

250
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:14,208
What just happened?

251
00:11:14,291 --> 00:11:15,791
She shot it
backwards into the net!

252
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:17,083
There's no way!

253
00:11:17,166 --> 00:11:19,000
